headline: 3 Reasons SNA is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Although the S&P 500 is down 3.6% over the past six months, Snap-on’s stock price has fallen further to $319.29, losing shareholders 14% of their capital. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
